pr_review_comment_body:
I think you can rewrite here a little bit:

    if response.status_code == 200:
        self.active = flag
        return True
    else:
        return False

This way all ``disable`` and `` enable``  code can be changed by

    def disable(self):
        return self._set_hook(False)

    def enable(self):
        return self._set_hook(True)

The tests should run with Python version 2.7 and 3.3+. So, either make an import for mock:

    try:
        from unittest import mock
    except ImportError:
        import mock

or use pytest's mocking facilities.

This will break the existing code that lets us prepopulate these fields (from $stateParams). e.g. from the "compare this revision in perfherder" link from the job details panel:

We probably need something like this:

```js
function getParameter(paramName, defaultValue) {
  if ($stateParams[paramName]) {
    return $stateParams[paramName];
  } else if (localStorageService.get(paramName) {
    return localStorageService.get(paramName);
  }

  return default;
}
```

Then you could just call that from each of the places. e.g. here:
```js
$scope.originalProject = _.findWhere(projects, {
  name: getParameter('originalProject', phCompareDefaultOriginalRepo),
  ...
});
```

Make sense?

